🐚We has such amazing clams in our recent trip to Spain that it was forever on our mind when we came back! We knew we had to make that dish one day and so viola!! I must say it was pretty close to what we ate and Super simple to whip up❤️Sharing with you guys the recipe below! ⁣
⁣
Ingredients: ⁣
1kg US Manila Clams, scrubbed and clean⁣
2 tbsp butter⁣
2 tbsp olive oil⁣
3-4 cloves of garlic, sliced⁣
1/4 cup white wine⁣
1/2 tsp salt⁣
1 tsp of cayenne pepper⁣
Juice of 1/4 a lemon⁣
1 tsp of Italian parsley, chopped finely ⁣
⁣
Steps:⁣
1)Heat olive oil and butter in a frying pan till butter melts.⁣
2)Add garlic and fry till slight brown and fragrant⁣
3)Add in the clams and quickly fry then and toss around⁣
4)Add in the white wine, salt, cayenne pepper ⁣
5)Cover the pan with a lid and cook the clams for 1-1.5 mins or until the clams open up⁣
6)Add in lemon juice and parsley. Give the clams a good toss and serve immediately with crusty bread!⁣
⁣
The best way to enjoy this is to grab some bread and soak up all the clam sauce! HEAVENLY!⁣
⁣
